  "summary": "IBM Watson Text to Speech converts text into natural‑sounding audio with neural voices, SSML support, and language coverage suitable for enterprise applications. Available through IBM Cloud, the service exposes REST/SDKs and supports common audio formats. Organizations pair TTS with other Watson services to build assistants, IVR, and e‑learning experiences. \n\nDevelopers select a voice and format, provide text/SSML, and retrieve synthesized audio; batch jobs and caching strategies support scale. IBM materials address governance and security expectations for enterprise rollouts and provide migration guidance from older services. Pricing is usage‑based with tiers for high‑volume workloads.\n\nWatson TTS is a fit for enterprises with existing IBM Cloud footprints or regulated requirements that benefit from IBM’s documentation and support.",
